channel.title: Please Help cant even run a script
channel.description: Hey guys.....I have SRL and followed starblasters fabulous tutorial and installed it correctly. Every time i go to run a script 10% of the time get a line error but 90% of the time i get the compiling failed error?? :( :( Please help. Also i thought the compiling error was there because i didnt have the proper includes but when i go to file>download includes the scar window freezes and i get Windows non responsive program errors, I would really appreciate some help guys!! thanks heaps. :confused: :confused: :confused:

item.dc:creator: @jason_x jason_x
item.description:
@jason_x wrote:

ok i think this is it so thanks if you can figure the error out

program PowerCutter;
procedure DropEm; forward;
procedure CutItDown; forward;
procedure FFight; forward;
procedure Report; forward;
procedure LogNewPlayer; forward;

{.include SRL\SRL.scar}
{.include SRL\SRL\skill\WoodCutting.scar}

const
TreeColour1 = 1651760; //The Colour of the tree your are cutting
TreeColour2 = 1453096; //Another Colour of the tree your are cutting, Plz choose colour near other colour you
//Picked for best results
TreeToCut = ‘Willow’; //The Name of the Tree You Are Cutting
StartPlayer = 0; //Player To Start With
LogsPerPlayer = 1000; //How many logs to cut before changing players

var
LogsChopped, TS, EXP: Integer;

procedure DeclarePlayers;
begin
HowManyPlayers := 1; // Set Number of Players here.
NumberOfPlayers(HowManyPlayers); // Sets the Players Array Length;
CurrentPlayer := StartPlayer; // CurrentPlayer = Array Index

Players[0].Name := ‘X Level X 3’; //Your Username
Players[0].Pass := ‘’; //Your Password
Players[0].Nick := ‘evel’; //3 or 4 letters from your Username
Players[0].Loc := ‘’; //Leave as blank
Players[0].Skill := ‘WoodCutting’; //The skill for when you get a lamp
Players[0].Active := True;

writeln(inttostr(HowManyPlayers) + ’ Players’);
end;

function TimeRunning1: string;
var
RHours, Minutes, Seconds, RMinutes, RSeconds: LongInt;
Time: string;
begin
Seconds := (GetSystemTime - TS) div 1000;
Minutes := Seconds div 60;
RHours := Minutes div 60;
Time := inttostr(Seconds) + ’ Seconds’;
if Minutes <> 0 then
begin
RSeconds := Seconds mod (Minutes * 60);
Time := inttostr(Minutes) + ’ Minutes and ’ + inttostr(RSeconds) + ’ Seconds’;
end;
if RHours <> 0 then
begin
RMinutes := Minutes mod (RHours * 60);
RSeconds := Seconds mod (Minutes * 60);
Time := inttostr(RHours) + ’ Hours, ’ + inttostr(RMinutes) +
’ Minutes and ’ + inttostr(RSeconds) + ’ Seconds’;
end;
Result := Time;
end;

function FindEnt1(TreeColor: Integer): Boolean;
var
i: Integer;
begin
if (Option2(‘Chop’)) then
begin
if (FindColorSpiralTolerance(x, y, 383705, 9, 9, 500, 24, 20)) or
(FindColorSpiralTolerance(x, y, 65535, 9, 9, 500, 24, 20)) then
begin
GetMousePos(x, y);
Mouse(x, y, 5, 5, false);
if (FindText(x, y, ‘Chop down’, UpChars, x - 50, y - 50, x + 50, y + 100)) then
begin
if (FindColor(x, y, 65535, x, y, x + 100, y + 25)) then
begin
for i := 1 to 2 do
begin
Mouse(648, 83, 1, 1, True)
Flag;
end;
WriteLn(‘Found ent! Waiting for it to go away’);
Wait(30000 + random(5000));
Result := True;
EntsAvoided := EntsAvoided + 1;
end;
end else
ChooseOption(x, y, ‘Cancel’);
end;
end;
end;

procedure LogIn;
begin
if (FindColor(x, y, 8353396, 262, 208, 262, 208)) then
begin
LogInPlayer;
end;
end;

procedure LogNewPlayer;
begin
LogOut;
NextPlayer(True);
LogIn;
TS := GetSystemTime;
LogsChopped := 0;
NickNameBMP := CreateBitmapMaskFromText(Players[CurrentPlayer].Nick, UpChars);
end;

procedure ChopTree(Colour1, Colour2: integer);
var
Waited4: integer;
begin
if FindColor(x, y, Colour1, 5, 5, 600, 600) then
begin
if FindColor(x, y, Colour2, x - 25, y - 25, x + 25, y + 25) then
begin
end;
MMouse(x, y, 5, 5);
GetMousePos(x, y);
wait(400);
if IsUpText('Chop down ’ + TreeToCut) then
begin
ClickMouse(x, y, true);
wait(1000);
Waited4 := 0;
repeat
FindEnt1(TreeColour1);
FindEnt1(TreeColour2);
FindHead;
FindNormalRandoms;
FFight;
InBlack;
FindPlant;
LogIn;
Waited4 := Waited4 + 1;
Report;
wait(300 + 100);
until ((not IsUpText('Chop down ’ + TreeToCut)) or (Waited4 > 15) or (InvFull));
end;
end;
end;

procedure FFight;
begin
if (FindFight) then
begin
Writeln(‘Found Fight’);
RunAwayDirection(‘W’);
Wait(8000 + random(3000));
RunBack;
if (WeAreDead) then
begin
Writeln(‘You Have Died…Changing Player’);
LogNewPlayer;
end;
end;
if (FindNewBox) then
begin
OpenBox;
SolveBox;
wait(1000);
if (FindNewBox) then
begin
GambleNewBox;
end;
if (FindNewBox) then
begin
LogOut;
Writeln(‘Unable To Solve Box…’);
LogNewPlayer;
end;
end;
end;

procedure CutItDown;
begin
while (not (InvFull)) do
begin
Status(‘Cutting Tree’);
ChopTree(TreeColour1, TreeColour2);
wait(1000);
LogIn;
Report;
end;
DropEm;
wait(1000);
end;

procedure DropEm;
var
rx, ry, m, n: Integer;
begin
Status(‘Dropping Logs’);
Gametab(4);
for M := 1 to 7 do
begin
for n := 1 to 4 do
begin
rx := 544 + (n * 42);
ry := 192 + (m * 36);
mmouse(rx, ry, 5, 5);
getmousepos(x, y);
wait(100 + random(100));
if (Not (IsUpText(‘Wield’))) then
begin
mouse(x, y, 0, 0, false);
wait(10 + random(50));
if (ClickText(‘Drop’, MIX1, MIY1, MIX2, MIY2)) then
begin
FindNormalRandoms;
FFight;
LogsChopped := LogsChopped + 1;
Report;
end;
end;
end;
end;
end;

procedure Report;
begin
if (not (LogsChopped >= LogsPerPlayer)) then
begin
Writeln(’<===========================================>’);
Writeln(’< You Are Using Nashi’‘s PowerCutter >’);
Writeln(’< ’ + Players[CurrentPlayer].Name + ’ Has…’);
Writeln(’< Cut ’ + IntToStr(LogsChopped) + ’ Logs!’);
Writeln(’< Gained ’ + IntToStr(LogsChopped * EXP) + ’ XP!’);
Writeln(’< Worked For ’ + TimeRunning1);
Writeln(’< ’ + TheTime + ’ >’);
Writeln(’<===========================================>’);
SRLRandomsReport;
end else
begin
Writeln(Players[CurrentPlayer].Name + ’ Has Finished Cutting…Changing Player’);
LogNewPlayer;
end;
end;

begin
BenMouse := True;
MouseSpeed := 1;
TS := GetSystemTime;
LogsChopped := 0;
if (TreeToCut = ‘Tree’) then
begin
EXP := 25;
end;
if (TreeToCut = ‘Oak’) then
begin
EXP := 37;
end;
if (TreeToCut = ‘Willow’) then
begin
EXP := 62;
end;
if (TreeToCut = ‘Teak’) then
begin
EXP := 100;
end;
if (TreeToCut = ‘Mahogany’) then
begin
EXP := 125;
end;
if (TreeToCut = ‘Yew’) then
begin
EXP := 175;
end;
if (TreeToCut = ‘Magic’) then
begin
EXP := 250;
end;
ClearDebug;
Writeln(‘Thank You For Using Nashi’‘s PowerChopper’);
Writeln(‘Hope You Dont Get Killed!’);
SetUpSRL;
DeclarePlayers;
DisguiseScar(‘No page to display - Microsoft Internet Explorer’);
LogIn;
FindAxeHeadColor;
NickNameBMP := CreateBitmapMaskFromText(Players[CurrentPlayer].Nick, UpChars);
repeat
CutItDown;
until (false);
end.
